<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">THE EASIEST WAY THROUGH THE FIRST FEW LEVELS</b></font> - <small>Tyrix, Erollisi Marr</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    In my experiences I have found that starting in Freeport is by far the quickest, being that you can get to level 12 in a day or two.

Start your bard, I picked a half elf.  Find your guild, it is in North Freeport.  Fight in the West Freeport newbie zone, snakes, decaying skeletons, bats, rats.  Sell what meager loot you get, and buy your first song -- Chant of Battle.  Now you're on your way to becoming a great bard.

Sing this song non-stop.  It gives you some STR and DEX, as well as increases your singing skill.  Fight in the newbie zone some more, until you hit level 2.  Buy your secong song -- Chords of Dissonance, and if you have extra money, buy your next few songs too, as the next couple levels should fly by also.

Go to east freeport, and zone into the Desert of North Ro.  Here you should fight Fire Beetles, Armadillo's, Spiderlings, basically anything that moves in the grassy area and the desert area by the zone.  You can easily get to level 4 here.

Now the fun begins.  Orc Raiders.  You can find a partner here, and go fight the Raiders, they con white to red, so watch out for the big ones.  You should twist chords of dissonance and your chant of battle.  Be careful with chords because it is a zone effect.

Once you hit level 5 you get probably the best bard song ever -- Selo's Accelerando -- aka SPEED SONG.  Go to your guild, buy a hand drum, and put a point into percussion.  Strap on that big bad hand drum, and fire up your Selo's, making haste back to North Ro.

Now if you are ballsy you can use your Chords of Dissonance and your Selo's Accelerando to kite bigger, harder mobs, such as the bigger or raiders and rattlesnakes, even pumas.  Using Selo's to run away, and singing the chords when then bad guy gets close enough, the running away some more.

At level 6 you get another utility song, Hymn of Restoration -- Heal Song!!!!  While twisting, Chant, Chords, and Heal Song, you should now be able to Melee the orc raiders, and the smaller rattle snakes, battling your way to level 7.

From here on the possibilities are endless, you can keep fighting pumas, raiders, and rattle snakes.  You could go to East commons and join an Orc hunting party, you could even sail across the ocean, and go to Crushbone.  Although I suggest staying in the freeport area and fighting orcs and such.

Good luck, and enjoy your bard, if you have any questions, contact me on Erollisi Marr.

--  Tyrix Truesong


    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
